model_filename = os.path.join(
        "./tensorflow/tensorflow/examples/label_image/data", 'quantized_graph_eightbit.pb')
    print model_filename
    with gfile.FastGFile(model_filename, 'rb') as f:
      graph_def = tf.GraphDef()
      graph_def.ParseFromString(f.read())
      writer=tf.train.write_graph(graph_def, './tensorflow/tensorflow/examples/label_image/data', 'quantized_graph.pb')

I print out the graph and load into tensorboard to visually check it and looks 2 pool layers

  • pool between conv_2 and conve_3

  • pool_1 between conv_4 and mixed

    goes away in the "quantized" version graph.

Is there any reason? I am quite new to tensor flow so there could be something wrong on my side.

Thanks.

body:
By doing this, 

```
model_filename = os.path.join(
        "./tensorflow/tensorflow/examples/label_image/data", 'quantized_graph_eightbit.pb')
    print model_filename
    with gfile.FastGFile(model_filename, 'rb') as f:
      graph_def = tf.GraphDef()
      graph_def.ParseFromString(f.read())
      writer=tf.train.write_graph(graph_def, './tensorflow/tensorflow/examples/label_image/data', 'quantized_graph.pb')
```

I print out the graph and load into tensorboard to visually check it and looks  2  pool layers
- pool between conv_2 and conve_3
- pool_1 between conv_4 and mixed
  
  goes away in the "quantized" version graph. 

Is there any reason? I am quite new to tensor flow so there could be something wrong on my side. 

Thanks.
